# Claude Code Instructions

## Agent Harness (NLAH)

This agent uses a modular Natural Language Agent Harness. CLAUDE.md is the loader --
behavioral rules live in `harness/` and are enforced by `core/contracts.py`.

### Module index

| Module | Path | What it defines |
|---|---|---|
| **Runtime** | `harness/_runtime.md` | Session lifecycle, git workflow, tool routing, default-to-action |
| **Contracts** | `harness/contracts/*.md` | Structured pre/post conditions with enforcement |
| **Skills** | `harness/skills/*.md` | Task-specific flows (customize for your use case) |
| **Failure taxonomy** | `harness/failure_modes/taxonomy.md` | Named failure modes with recovery paths |
| **Code enforcement** | `core/contracts.py` | Python Contract classes -- deterministic gates |

### Active contracts (code-enforced in `core/contracts.py`)

| Contract | Failure mode | What it blocks |
|---|---|---|
| `verify-before-push` | FM-002 | Push without verification output |
| `pre-denial-gate` | FM-001 | "I can't" without smoke test |
